The '''2008&ndash;09 season''' is be the 87th season in '''York City F.C. '''<U+2019>s history, and their fifth in the [[Conference National]].

==Background==
[[Coach (sport)|Manager]] [[Billy McEwan (footballer born 1951)| Billy McEwan]] was sacked early in the 2007&ndash;08 season with the team in 19th place in the table and having recently been beaten by [[Conference South]] side [[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.| Havant & Waterlooville]] in the [[FA Cup]].<ref name="York City sack Billy McEwan">{{cite news
| first = Steve
| last = Carroll
| title = York City sack Billy McEwan
| url = http://www.thepress.co.uk/search/1842841.York_City_sack_Billy_McEwan/
| publisher = The Press
| date = [[2007-11-19]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> After an unbeaten spell as caretaker manager, [[Colin Walker (footballer born 1958)|Colin Walker]] was appointed as York<U+2019>s permanent manager and led the team to a 14th place finish in the Conference.<ref name="Walker handed York manager's job">{{cite news
| title = Walker handed York manager's job
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/y/york_city/7161250.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2007-12-27]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref><ref name="Final 2007/2008 Football Conference Table">{{cite web
| title = Final 2007/2008 Football Conference Table
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/league2.sd?competitionid=7&seasonid=137&teamid=2910
| publisher = Soccerbase
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> [[Darren Craddock]], [[Stuart Elliott (footballer born 1977)|Stuart Elliott]] and [[Tom Evans (footballer)|Tom Evans]] were initially released by the club,<ref name="Three players released by Walker">{{cite news
| title = Three players released by Walker
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/y/york_city/7364935.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2008-04-24]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> which was followed by the exits of [[Ross Greenwood (footballer)|Ross Greenwood]], Chris Hall, [[Anthony Lloyd]], [[captain (football)|captain]] [[Emmanuel Panther]] and Alex Rhodes.<ref name="Panther packed off">{{cite news
| first = Dave
| last = Flett
| title = Panther packed off
| url = http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/news/display.var.2228032.0.panther_packed_off.php
| publisher = The Press
| date = [[2008-04-26]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> Professional contracts were handed to youngsters Andy McWilliams, Danny Radcliffe and Liam Shepherd in May,<ref name="Youth team players sign for York">{{cite news
| title = Youth team players sign for York
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/y/york_city/7386495.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2008-05-07]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> which was followed by the arrivals [[Mark Greaves]] and [[Michael Ingham (footballer)|Michael Ingham]],<ref name="York City sign Greaves and Ingham">{{cite news
| title = York City sign Greaves and Ingham
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/y/york_city/7401785.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2008-05-15]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> as well as the departure of [[Nicky Wroe]] to [[Torquay United F.C.|Torquay United]].<ref name="Torquay sign Wroe from York City">{{cite news
| title = Torquay sign Wroe from York City
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/t/torquay_united/7423921.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2008-05-28]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> June saw the arrivals of [[Ben Wilkinson]], [[Steven Hogg]], [[Niall Henderson]] and former loanee [[Daniel McBreen]].<ref name="York City clinch double signing">{{cite news
| title = York City clinch double signing
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/y/york_city/7448327.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2008-06-11]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref><ref name="Minstermen move in for Henderson">{{cite news
| title = Minstermen move in for Henderson
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/y/york_city/7463342.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2008-06-19]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref><ref name="York sign Iron striker McBreen">{{cite news
| title = York sign Iron striker McBreen
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/y/york_city/7475212.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2008-06-26]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref>

==Review==
===Pre-season===
New signing Greaves was named as York<U+2019>s captain for the season before beginning their pre-season campaign with a 6&ndash;0 win over [[Tadcaster Albion A.F.C.|Tadcaster Albion]], which featured trialists [[David Brown (footballer born 1989)|David Brown]], [[Nathan Fisher]] and Anton Foster.<ref name="Brown stakes claim to be a full-time Minsterman">{{cite news
| first = Dave
| last = Flett
| title = Brown stakes claim to be a full-time Minsterman
| url = http://www.thepress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/3197703.Brown_stakes_claim_to_be_a_full_time_Minsterman/
| publisher = The Press
| date = [[2008-07-08]]
| accessdate = 2008-07-08}}</ref><ref name="City boss weighs up final signing to bolster squad">{{cite news
| first = Dave
| last = Flett
| title = City boss weighs up final signing to bolster squad
| url = http://www.thepress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/3199036.City_boss_weighs_up_final_signing_to_bolster_squad/
| publisher = The Press
| date = [[2008-07-09]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> However, Walker later said that the trialists were only in the squad to make up the numbers and were unlikely to be signed.<ref name="York squad is complete - Walker">{{cite news
| title = York squad is complete - Walker
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/y/york_city/7499675.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2008-07-10]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> Despite this, former [[Exeter City F.C.|Exeter City]] [[midfielder#Winger|winger]] [[Lee Elam]] featured in a 1&ndash;1 draw against [[Leeds United A.F.C.|Leeds United]].<ref name="Teenage power provides a welcome tonic for Walker">{{cite news
| first = Dave
| last = Flett
| title = Teenage power provides a welcome tonic for Walker
| url = http://www.thepress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/3204209.Teenage_power_provides_a_welcome_tonic_for_Walker/
| publisher = The Press
| date = [[2008-07-12]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> [[David Wheater]] scored a late equaliser for [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] as York finished with a 2&ndash;2 draw against the [[Premier League]] side, which Elam again played in.<ref name="Teenage striker Boyes excels">{{cite news
| first = Dave
| last = Flett
| title = Teenage striker Boyes excels
| url = http://www.thepress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/3218014.Teenage_striker_Boyes_excels/
| publisher = The Press
| date = [[2008-07-19]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> York<U+2019>s next friendly was against last season<U+2019>s FA Cup semi-finalists, [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]], which was again a 2&ndash;2 draw. <ref name="York impress again in pre-season">{{cite news
| title = York impress again in pre-season
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/y/york_city/7520643.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2008-07-23]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> Walker confirmed that Elam would not be given a contract with York,<ref name="No deal for Elam">{{cite news
| first = Steve
| last = Carroll
| title = No deal for Elam
| url = http://www.thepress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/3226361.No_deal_for_Elam/
| publisher = The Press
| date = [[2008-07-23]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> and he later joined fellow Conference side [[Altrincham F.C.|Altrincham]].<ref name="Elam joins Altrincham part-time">{{cite news
| title = Elam joins Altrincham part-time
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/a/altrincham/7526924.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2008-07-26]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> A 2&ndash;1 victory against [[Harrogate Railway Athletic F.C.|Harrogate Railway Athletic]] saw [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] Michael Ingham suffer a thigh injury,<ref name="Minstermen<U+2019>s anxious vigil over <U+2019>keeper<U+2019>s fitness">{{cite news
| first = Peter
| last = Martini
| title = Minstermen<U+2019>s anxious vigil over <U+2019>keeper<U+2019>s fitness
| url = http://www.thepress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/3549150.Minstermen___s_anxious_vigil_over____keeper___s_fitness_/
| publisher = The Press
| date = [[2008-07-26]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> meaning he missed the game against [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]],<ref name="Anxious City monitor star stopper<U+2019>s thigh injury">{{cite news
| first = Steve
| last = Carroll
| title = Anxious City monitor star stopper<U+2019>s thigh injury
| url = http://www.thepress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/3554853.Anxious_City_monitor_star_stopper___s_thigh_injury/
| publisher = The Press
| date = [[2008-07-29]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> which gave Josh Mimms the chance to play and the match ended as a 1&ndash;0 victory for York.<ref name="City teenage defender in frame for Crawley opener">{{cite news
| first = Dave
| last = Flett
| title = City teenage defender in frame for Crawley opener
| url = http://www.thepress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/3559492.City_teenage_defender_in_frame_for_Crawley_opener/
| publisher = The Press
| date = [[2008-07-31]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref> A 1&ndash;0 victory, due to a [[David McGurk]] goal against [[Sheffield F.C.|Sheffield]] meant York finished the pre-season campaign unbeaten.<ref name="McGurk hits late winner">{{cite news
| title = McGurk hits late winner
| url = http://york.rivals.net/News/pgArticle.aspx?artid=13834_3902163&id=100
| publisher = minstermen.net
| date = [[2008-08-03]]
| accessdate = 2008-08-03}}</ref>

